710486f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 20th Street (West)
710486f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, at W. 20th Street, showing buildings
at the S. W. and N. W. corners. That at the former is under de-
molition. The photographer is east of the Avenue and is viewing
westward towards the North (Hudson) River.
March 3, 1929
July 16, 1932
P. L. Sperr

710489f-a.title: Manhattan: 10th Avenue - 20th Street (West)
710489f-a.text:
Tenth Avenue, west side, north from West 20th to 21st Streets.
Note at the extreme right, the tenement at the N. W. oorner of 21st
Street. This was demolished and the ew Roman Catholic Church of the
Guardiar Angel erected there. This organization was formerly located
at No. 511-5 W. 23rd Street. Demolition of their church there, for
the new New York Central Railroad elevated roadbed,necessitated this
Nnew structure.
March 3, 1929
July 28, 1931
P. L. Sperr
